modules.description: Tracks numeric values, counters, and timing data from specific program points, using tagged sources for fine-grained control. Operates on mutable state and closures to collect and aggregate metrics efficiently. Enables real-time performance tracking in production environments, such as measuring request latencies or counting error occurrences.

Encodes metrics into InfluxDB line protocol using specified tags, data, and measurement names. Tracks and reports metrics at defined intervals, supporting optional tag prefixes. Designed for real-time monitoring systems requiring structured time-series data output.
